	<body>
		<h1>slider(varname)<br>slider(varname,textleft,textright) </h1>

		<div id="abstract">
		Displays a horizontal slider, which can be dragged by the user to take a value between 0 (leftmost position) and 1 (rightmost position). The value 
		is stored to the variable whenever the user moves the slider. Note that the value will always be between 0 and 1, regardless of what you specify using 
		textleft and textright. If you want a different scale, for example payment amounts, you can do the conversion after the wait() command.
		</div>


		<h2>Parameters</h2>
		<div id="parameters">
		<table>
			<tr><td width=200>varname</td><td width=600>The name of the variable in which the result is stored.</td></tr>
			<tr><td width=200>textleft</td><td width=600>Optional. A text, which is displayed to the left of the slider.</td></tr>
			<tr><td width=200>textright</td><td width=600>Optional. A text, which is displayed to the right of the slider.</td></tr>
		</table>
		</div>

		<h2>See also</h2>
		<a target="Main" href="assert.html">assert</a>,
		<a target="Main" href="choice.html">choice</a>,
		<a target="Main" href="inputNumber.html">inputNumber</a>



		<h2>Examples</h2>
		<h3>Basic string input</h3>
		<table>
			<tr>
				<td width=500 valign=top>
					<img src="img/slider1c.png">
				</td>
				<td width=300 valign=top>
					<img src="img/slider1e.png"> <br>
					<img src="img/slider1e2.png"> <br>
					(Corresponding recorded values).
				</td>
			</tr>
		</table>



